==Usage==
This template formats IPA transcriptions and links them to [[Help:IPA/Astur-Leonese]]. The transcription should match the conventions of that key; for narrower dialect transcriptions, use {{tl|IPA-all}}, which links to a more complete IPA key. 

The first cell in the template is for the transcription, and a second optional cell is a switch that controls the lede. With no second value, the lede ''Asturian pronunciation:'' appears: 
*<code><nowiki>{{IPA-ast|tu}}</nowiki></code> → {{IPA-ast|tu}}
*<code><nowiki>{{IPA-ast|tu|pron}}</nowiki></code> → {{IPA-ast|tu|pron}}
*<code><nowiki>{{IPA-ast|tu|lang}}</nowiki></code> → {{IPA-ast|tu|lang}}
*<code><nowiki>{{IPA-ast|tu|local}}</nowiki></code> → {{IPA-ast|tu|local}}
*<code><nowiki>{{IPA-ast|tu|IPA}}</nowiki></code> → {{IPA-ast|tu|IPA}}
*<code><nowiki>{{IPA-ast|tu|}}</nowiki></code> → {{IPA-ast|tu|}}

Any of these may be combined with a sound file in an optional third cell:
*<code><nowiki>{{IPA-ast|tu|IPA|Es-tú.ogg}}</nowiki></code> → {{IPA-ast|tu|IPA|Es-tú.ogg}}

For the default lede, however, a placeholder such as ‹-› is required in the second cell: 
*<code><nowiki>{{IPA-ast|tu|-|Es-tú.ogg}}</nowiki></code> → {{IPA-ast|tu|-|Es-tú.ogg}}

